# Git Scout — Environment Configuration Example
#
# NOTE: Git Scout is a browser-only Single Page Application (SPA).
# By default, you do NOT need a .env file! Users can enter their API keys
# and GitHub Access Token directly inside the settings modal in the web UI,
# and they will be saved securely in their browser's local storage.
#
# If you are developing or hosting your own copy and want to pre-configure
# environment variables, you can create a `.env` file in this directory
# with the following structure:

# GitHub Personal Access Token (for increasing API rate limits)
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=

# AI Provider API Keys
VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
